folder: Metropolitan Avenue & Fresh Pond Road, Queens, NY
original_title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Fresh Pond Road
text:
Metropolitan Avenue, at the S.E. corner of Fresh Pond Road, showing at the corner the Bushwick Station of the Long Island Railroad. This area consisting of 7 3/4 acres was purchased by one Braujes on June 26, 1862 for 5,252 dollars. About 1 3/4 acres were sold to the Long Island Railroad for about the above amount and the remainder in 1909 to the Bushwick Junction Real Estate Co. for $50,000.

1922

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Metropolitan Avenue, south side, between Fresh Pond Road and 61st Street, showing in their order from fore to background places either owned or belonging to the following people in 1873, namely; Harness Shop, J.H. Ellinger, a harness maker; Lipman; F. Eberle, owned by one Jacob, and Jacob's Saloon.

1922

original_title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Fresh Pond Road
text:
Metropolitan Avenue, north side, west of Fresh Pond Road, showing the Ditmars house occupying land owned by C.N. Ditmars in 1852. This house stands near the site of the old house which in 1877 was on the east side of Hunters Point Turnpike.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
